In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses several topics. He begins by mentioning President Obama's commitment to bring America's classrooms into the 21st century, with high-speed Internet and cutting-edge technology. Carney then announces that Adobe and Prezi will be making free software available to teachers and students to help introduce creative learning materials to classrooms across the country. He also addresses the situation in Ukraine, expressing concern about reports of Russian intervention in Crimea and calling on Russia to respect Ukraine's territorial integrity. Carney does not speculate on what actions the US might take if Russia were to cross a line, but emphasizes the importance of maintaining Ukraine's sovereignty. He also briefly discusses other topics such as the EPA's announcement about protecting a fishery in Alaska, the President's upcoming speech, and the President's views on the Koch brothers and un-American activities.